{
  "response": "# Multi-Step Healthcare Registration Form Accessibility Design Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** Use a11y-planner protocol. Review with a11y-critic after implementation.  \n> **Compliance target:** WCAG 2.2 AA  \n> **Users who need accessibility:** Screen reader users, keyboard-only users, low vision users, cognitive accessibility users, users with color vision differences  \n> **Assistive technologies:** NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver, keyboard-only navigation  \n\n**Feature:** A four-step healthcare portal registration form with inline validation, step-level error summaries, and final cross-step error consolidation.  \n**Risk Level:** High  \n**Component/Page Type:** Multi-step form, inline validation, error summary, wizard navigation, final review/submit  \n\n---\n\n## Scope & Context\n\nThis plan covers the accessible error communication system for an existing React SPA registration form using React Hook Form. The form has four steps:\n\n1. Personal info\n2. Insurance details\n3. Medical history\n4. Review/submit\n\nEach step has 4-8 fields. Validation occurs in two modes:\n\n- **Blur-time inline validation:** field-level validation after a user leaves a field.\n- **Submit-time step validation:** all errors on the current step surface when the user attempts to advance.\n- **Final submit validation:** the review step checks for incomplete required fields across all previous steps and shows a consolidated cross-step error list.\n\nExisting visual error treatments must remain:\n\n- Red left border on invalid field\n- Red error message below the field\n- Red label text\n\nThese are not sufficient by themselves because color is currently the only error cue. This plan adds programmatic error communication, non-color visual indicators, focus behavior, and summary navigation.\n\nCore WCAG requirements:\n\n- **WCAG 1.3.1 Info and Relationships:** errors, labels, hints, and required state must be programmatically associated with fields.\n- **WCAG 1.4.1 Use of Color:** red border/text cannot be the only error indicator.\n- **WCAG 2.1.1 Keyboard:** all fields, summary links, and step controls must be operable by keyboard.\n- **WCAG 2.4.3 Focus Order:** focus must move predictably after failed validation and cross-step navigation.\n- **WCAG 2.4.7 Focus Visible:** focused inputs, buttons, and error links must have visible focus indicators.\n- **WCAG 3.3.1 Error Identification:** users must know which fields are invalid.\n- **WCAG 3.3.2 Labels or Instructions:** fields must include clear labels and format requirements.\n- **WCAG 3.3.3 Error Suggestion:** error messages should explain how to fix the problem.\n- **WCAG 3.3.7 Redundant Entry:** previously entered information must persist across steps.\n- **WCAG 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value:** invalid/required/disabled states must be programmatically determinable.\n- **WCAG 4.1.3 Status Messages:** validation summaries and dynamic error count changes must be announced appropriately.\n\nThis plan is not claiming to cover server-side validation, backend submission failures, authentication, appointment scheduling, or medical record content accessibility beyond the registration fields.\n\n---\n\n## Semantic Structure Plan\n\nThe form should use native form semantics first. ARIA should supplement native semantics only where state, summary behavior, or dynamic messaging requires it.\n\n### Page and Step Structure\n\nThe SPA page should expose a stable document structure:\n\n```html\n<body>\n  <a href=\"#main-content\" class=\"skip-link\">Skip to main content</a>\n\n  <main id=\"main-content\">\n    <h1>Register for the healthcare portal</h1>\n\n    <nav aria-label=\"Registration progress\">\n      <!-- step list -->\n    </nav>\n\n    <form aria-labelledby=\"registration-heading\" novalidate>\n      <h2 id=\"registration-heading\">Step 1 of 4: Personal info</h2>\n\n      <!-- step-level error summary appears here when needed -->\n\n      <fieldset>\n        <legend>Personal info</legend>\n\n        <!-- form fields -->\n      </fieldset>\n\n      <div aria-label=\"Step actions\">\n        <!-- Back / Continue / Submit buttons -->\n      </div>\n    </form>\n  </main>\n</body>\n```\n\nSemantic requirements:\n\n| Area | Required Semantics | WCAG Citation |\n|---|---|---|\n| Main content | `main` with stable `id` target | 1.3.1, 2.4.1 |\n| Page title | One clear `h1` | 1.3.1, 2.4.6 |\n| Current step heading | `h2`, updated per step | 1.3.1, 2.4.6 |\n| Step progress | `nav aria-label=\"Registration progress\"` with ordered list | 1.3.1, 2.4.5 |\n| Step fields | `fieldset` and `legend` per logical step | 1.3.1 |\n| Field labels | Visible `<label for=\"...\">` for every input | 1.3.1, 2.4.6, 3.3.2 |\n| Error messages | Persistent elements with stable IDs, referenced by inputs | 1.3.1, 3.3.1 |\n| Error summary | Programmatically named region at top of step | 1.3.1, 3.3.1, 4.1.3 |\n\n### Field Structure Stub\n\nEach field should follow this structure conceptually:\n\n```html\n<div class=\"field field--error\">\n  <label for=\"date-of-birth\">\n    Date of birth\n    <span aria-hidden=\"true\">*</span>\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">required</span>\n  </label>\n\n  <p id=\"date-of-birth-hint\">Use MM/DD/YYYY format.</p>\n\n  <input\n    id=\"date-of-birth\"\n    name=\"dateOfBirth\"\n    aria-required=\"true\"\n    aria-invalid=\"true\"\n    aria-describedby=\"date-of-birth-hint date-of-birth-error\"\n  />\n\n  <p id=\"date-of-birth-error\">\n    <span aria-hidden=\"true\">!</span>\n    Date of birth is required. Enter a date in MM/DD/YYYY format.\n  </p>\n</div>\n```\n\nImportant boundary: the exact markup can vary by component library, but the accessible relationships cannot vary. The input must own the error relationship through `aria-describedby`.\n\n---\n\n## Interaction Pattern Design\n\nThis form mostly uses native form controls, which is the correct pattern. The custom parts are the step navigation, error summary, and cross-step error links.\n\n### Interactive Elements Table\n\n| Widget | APG Pattern | Keyboard Model | ARIA Attributes | WCAG Citation |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Text input, date input, select, checkbox, radio | Native HTML form controls, not custom ARIA widgets | Tab/Shift+Tab moves through fields. Native controls use platform keys. | `aria-invalid`, `aria-describedby`, `aria-required` where needed | 1.3.1, 2.1.1, 3.3.1, 3.3.2, 4.1.2 |\n| Continue button | APG Button pattern: https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/button/ | Tab to button. Enter/Space activates. | Native `button`; `disabled` only when truly unavailable | 2.1.1, 4.1.2 |\n| Back button | APG Button pattern | Tab to button. Enter/Space activates. | Native `button` | 2.1.1, 2.4.3 |\n| Final submit button | APG Button pattern | Tab to button. Enter/Space activates. | Native submit button; loading state may use `aria-busy` on form/status region | 2.1.1, 4.1.2, 4.1.3 |\n| Step progress links/buttons | APG Button or Link pattern depending on behavior | Tab to reachable step. Enter activates. | `aria-current=\"step\"` on current step indicator | 2.1.1, 2.4.4, 4.1.2 |\n| Step-level error summary links | Native Link pattern | Tab to link. Enter navigates and focuses invalid field. | Link text names field and error. Optional `aria-describedby` to summary intro if needed. | 2.1.1, 2.4.4, 2.4.3, 3.3.1 |\n| Cross-step consolidated error links | Native Link pattern with SPA navigation behavior | Enter navigates to correct step, then focuses target field. | Link text includes step name, field name, and error. | 2.1.1, 2.4.4, 2.4.3, 3.3.1 |\n| Error summary container | Status/alert pattern, not a dialog | Appears at top of step. Focus moves to summary after failed step advance/final submit. | `role=\"alert\"` or `aria-live=\"assertive\"` for submit-time summaries; `tabindex=\"-1\"` for programmatic focus | 3.3.1, 4.1.3, 2.4.3 |\n\n### APG Pattern Notes\n\nThe error summary is not a modal, disclosure, tab panel, or menu. Do not invent a composite widget. It is a dynamically inserted alert/status region containing normal links.\n\nFor step progress, avoid APG Tabs unless all steps are simultaneously available as tab panels and arrow-key navigation is intentionally implemented. In this healthcare registration flow, step navigation behaves like wizard navigation, so use regular buttons/links and `aria-current=\"step\"` rather than tab roles.\n\n---\n\n## ARIA Implementation Plan\n\n### Required Field ARIA\n\nFor each invalid field:\n\n- `aria-invalid=\"true\"` on the invalid input.\n  - WCAG: 3.3.1 Error Identification, 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value.\n- `aria-describedby` must include:\n  - hint/instruction ID, if present;\n  - error message ID, when invalid.\n  - WCAG: 1.3.1 Info and Relationships, 3.3.2 Labels or Instructions, 3.3.1 Error Identification.\n- `aria-required=\"true\"` may be used when required state is not otherwise communicated by native `required`.\n  - WCAG: 3.3.2, 4.1.2.\n- Native `required` is acceptable, but because React Hook Form custom validation is already in use, do not rely on browser validation UI. Keep `novalidate` on the form and implement custom accessible messaging.\n\nFor valid fields:\n\n- Omit `aria-invalid` or set `aria-invalid=\"false\"`.\n- Keep `aria-describedby` connected to persistent hints.\n- Remove the error message ID from `aria-describedby` when no error exists, unless the error element remains present and empty. Prefer removing the error ID to avoid stale announcements.\n\n### Error Message IDs\n\nEvery field error must have a stable, deterministic ID:\n\n- `first-name-error`\n- `insurance-member-id-error`\n- `medical-history-allergies-error`\n\nReact Hook Form field names can be used to derive IDs, but generated IDs must be stable across re-renders.\n\n### Error Summary ARIA\n\nStep-level summary:\n\n```html\n<div\n  id=\"step-error-summary\"\n  role=\"alert\"\n  tabindex=\"-1\"\n  aria-labelledby=\"step-error-summary-heading\"\n>\n  <h3 id=\"step-error-summary-heading\">3 errors on this page</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li><a href=\"#date-of-birth\">Date of birth is required.</a></li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n```\n\nCross-step final summary:\n\n```html\n<div\n  id=\"final-error-summary\"\n  role=\"alert\"\n  tabindex=\"-1\"\n  aria-labelledby=\"final-error-summary-heading\"\n>\n  <h3 id=\"final-error-summary-heading\">7 errors must be fixed before submitting</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>\n      <a href=\"#insurance-member-id\" data-step=\"insurance\">\n        Insurance details: Member ID is required.\n      </a>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n```\n\nUse `role=\"alert\"` for submit-time and failed-step-advance summaries because they are user-triggered validation failures requiring immediate attention.\n\nDo not use `role=\"alert\"` on every inline field error. That creates repeated assertive announcements and can become disruptive. This is a deliberate constraint.\n\nWCAG citations:\n\n- `role=\"alert\"` / assertive summary: WCAG 4.1.3 Status Messages.\n- `tabindex=\"-1\"` for focus target: WCAG 2.4.3 Focus Order.\n- Summary links: WCAG 2.4.4 Link Purpose, 3.3.1 Error Identification.\n\n---\n\n## Keyboard Interaction Model\n\n### Standard Form Navigation\n\n- `Tab`: moves to the next input, select, checkbox, radio group, summary link, or button in DOM order.\n- `Shift+Tab`: moves backward.\n- `Enter`:\n  - In text fields, should not accidentally advance the step unless the product explicitly supports Enter-to-continue and validation behavior is identical to Continue.\n  - On buttons/links, activates the control.\n- `Space`:\n  - Activates buttons.\n  - Toggles checkboxes/radios according to native behavior.\n- Arrow keys:\n  - Use native behavior for radio groups/selects.\n  - No custom roving tabindex is needed unless a custom radio/listbox component exists.\n\n### Error Summary Links\n\nWhen a keyboard user activates a summary link:\n\n1. If the target field is on the current step:\n   - Scroll the field into view.\n   - Move programmatic focus to the actual invalid input, not the wrapper and not the error text.\n2. If the target field is on another step:\n   - Navigate to the target step.\n   - Render the step.\n   - After render completes, scroll and focus the invalid input.\n   - Preserve existing form values and validation state.\n\nThis is required for WCAG 2.4.3 Focus Order and WCAG 3.3.1 Error Identification.\n\n### Step Navigation With Errors\n\nWhen the user presses Continue and the current step has errors:\n\n1. Prevent step advancement.\n2. Render/update the step-level error summary at the top of the step.\n3. Move focus to the summary container.\n4. The summary heading announces the count.\n5. The user can Tab into the list of error links and activate a link to focus the relevant field.\n\nFocus must not remain on the Continue button after failed validation. That leaves screen reader and keyboard users without immediate context.\n\nWhen the current step has no errors:\n\n1. Advance to the next step.\n2. Move focus to the new step heading or first field.\n3. Recommended: focus the new step heading with `tabindex=\"-1\"` so the user hears \u201cStep 2 of 4: Insurance details.\u201d\n4. Do not auto-focus the first input if doing so skips the step context.\n\n---\n\n## Focus Management Plan\n\n### Initial Page Load\n\nFocus remains wherever the browser places it. The first keyboard focus should be the skip link. The main form heading should be reachable as the skip target.\n\n### Step Change Success\n\nOn successful step advancement:\n\n- Update the `h2` text to the new step name.\n- Move focus to the step heading with `tabindex=\"-1\"`.\n- Announce step context through the heading text: \u201cStep 2 of 4: Insurance details.\u201d\n- Keep data from previous steps intact.\n\nWCAG: 2.4.3 Focus Order, 2.4.6 Headings and Labels, 3.3.7 Redundant Entry.\n\n### Step Change Failure\n\nOn failed Continue:\n\n- Keep user on the current step.\n- Insert or update the step-level error summary.\n- Move focus to the summary container.\n- Summary must be programmatically focusable with `tabindex=\"-1\"`.\n- The summary must include links to each invalid field.\n\nWCAG: 2.4.3, 3.3.1, 4.1.3.\n\n### Blur-Time Inline Validation\n\nBlur-time validation should not steal focus. When a user tabs away from a field and an error appears:\n\n- Keep focus on the next element.\n- Display the inline error visually.\n- Add `aria-invalid=\"true\"` and connect the error through `aria-describedby`.\n- Do not use `role=\"alert\"` on the inline error.\n- Recommended: use a single polite status region for concise blur-time validation only when necessary.\n\nBlur-time announcement strategy:\n\n```html\n<div id=\"form-validation-status\" role=\"status\" aria-live=\"polite\"></div>\n```\n\nBehavior:\n\n- On blur, update the polite status with a short message such as \u201cDate of birth has an error.\u201d\n- Debounce by approximately 500ms so rapid tabbing does not queue excessive announcements.\n- Do not repeat the full error text in the live region if it is already associated with the field.\n- On refocus, the input\u2019s `aria-describedby` causes the full error to be available.\n\nThis avoids the below-expectation pattern of assertive alerts firing after every field blur.\n\nWCAG: 3.3.1, 3.3.3, 4.1.3.\n\n### Final Cross-Step Errors\n\nOn final submit with errors across prior steps:\n\n1. Keep the user on the review/submit step initially.\n2. Render the consolidated error summary.\n3. Move focus to the consolidated summary.\n4. Each error link includes the step name and field error.\n5. Activating a link navigates to the correct step, then focuses the field.\n\nImplementation must store focus intent before navigation:\n\n- Target step\n- Target field ID\n- Optional target error ID\n\nAfter the step renders, apply focus to the field. In React, this usually requires a post-render effect keyed by the target step/field intent.\n\nWCAG: 2.4.3, 3.3.1, 3.3.3, 4.1.3.\n\n---\n\n## State Communication Design\n\n### State Communication Table\n\n| State | Visual Indicator | Programmatic Indicator | ARIA / Attribute | WCAG Citation |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Required field | Asterisk plus visible/hidden \u201crequired\u201d text | Required state available to AT | `required` or `aria-required=\"true\"` | 3.3.2, 4.1.2 |\n| Valid field | Normal border, normal label | No invalid state | Omit `aria-invalid` or set `false` | 4.1.2 |\n| Invalid field | Red left border, red label, error text, error icon | Invalid state and associated error text | `aria-invalid=\"true\"`, `aria-describedby=\"hint-id error-id\"` | 1.3.1, 3.3.1, 4.1.2 |\n| Inline blur error appears | Error message below field, icon | Polite status update; field association | Single `role=\"status\"` region; no per-field alert | 3.3.1, 4.1.3 |\n| Step submit errors | Error summary at top with count and links | Assertive summary announcement and focus | `role=\"alert\"`, `tabindex=\"-1\"` | 3.3.1, 4.1.3, 2.4.3 |\n| Cross-step final errors | Consolidated error list with step labels | Assertive summary announcement and focus | `role=\"alert\"`, link targets with navigation/focus intent | 3.3.1, 3.3.3, 4.1.3 |\n| Disabled Continue/Submit, if used | Disabled styling plus text reason where needed | Native disabled state | `disabled` on native button | 4.1.2 |\n| Loading validation, if async added later | Spinner plus text \u201cChecking\u2026\u201d | Busy/status state | `aria-busy=\"true\"` on form section; `role=\"status\"` text | 4.1.3 |\n| Current step | Step indicator style | Current step conveyed programmatically | `aria-current=\"step\"` | 1.3.1, 4.1.2 |\n| Completed step | Check icon plus \u201cComplete\u201d text | Textual status in progress item | Visible or visually hidden \u201cComplete\u201d | 1.3.1, 1.4.1 |\n\n### Non-Color Error Indicator\n\nThe existing red border, red label, and red error text must remain, but cannot be the only indicator.\n\nAdd at least one non-color indicator:\n\n- Error icon next to the error message, such as a warning triangle.\n- Visible text such as \u201cError:\u201d before the message.\n- Left border may remain red, but the icon/text makes the state understandable without color.\n\nRecommended error message format:\n\n```text\nError: Date of birth is required. Enter a date in MM/DD/YYYY format.\n```\n\nThe icon should be decorative if the text says \u201cError.\u201d If using a symbol, wrap it with `aria-hidden=\"true\"` so screen readers do not announce \u201cwarning sign\u201d redundantly.\n\nWCAG: 1.4.1 Use of Color, 3.3.1 Error Identification.\n\n---\n\n## Cognitive Load Strategy\n\nThere is a real tradeoff here.\n\nShowing every error at once helps users understand total work remaining and supports direct navigation. But long lists can overwhelm users, especially in healthcare contexts where fields may be sensitive or cognitively demanding.\n\nRecommended approach:\n\n- **On blur:** show only the field\u2019s own inline error. Do not open the summary.\n- **On failed step advancement:** show all errors for the current step in the step summary.\n- **On final submit:** show all blocking errors across all steps, grouped by step.\n- **Do not progressively reveal only one error at a time** after submit, because users may fix one field only to discover another later. That increases effort and can feel punitive.\n- **Do group cross-step errors by step** to reduce cognitive load.\n\nFinal summary structure:\n\n```text\n7 errors must be fixed before submitting\n\nPersonal info\n- Date of birth is required.\n- Phone number must include 10 digits.\n\nInsurance details\n- Member ID is required.\n\nMedical history\n- Allergy response is required.\n```\n\nThis balances completeness with scanability.\n\nWCAG: 3.3.1 Error Identification, 3.3.3 Error Suggestion, 3.3.7 Redundant Entry.\n\n---\n\n## Visual Accessibility Plan\n\n### Error Styling\n\nCurrent red treatments may remain, but add:\n\n- Error icon or \u201cError:\u201d text.\n- Sufficient contrast for red text against background: at least 4.5:1 for normal text.\n- Error border/icon contrast at least 3:1 against adjacent colors.\n\nWCAG: 1.4.1, 1.4.3, 1.4.11.\n\n### Focus Indicators\n\nAll inputs, buttons, progress controls, and summary links need visible focus.\n\nRequirements:\n\n- Use `:focus-visible`.\n- Minimum 3:1 contrast against adjacent colors.\n- Prefer a two-color focus indicator so it remains visible on light and dark backgrounds.\n- Focus must not be hidden under sticky headers.\n- Error summary focus state must be visible when focus is moved there.\n\nWCAG: 2.4.7 Focus Visible, 2.4.11 Focus Not Obscured, 2.4.13 Focus Appearance.\n\n### Text and Zoom\n\n- Use relative units for text.\n- Layout must work at 200% zoom and 320 CSS px equivalent width without horizontal scrolling.\n- Error summaries must wrap cleanly.\n- Long healthcare or insurance field names must not overflow.\n- Touch/click targets should be at least 24x24 CSS px minimum, 44x44 recommended.\n\nWCAG: 1.4.4 Resize Text, 1.4.10 Reflow, 2.5.8 Target Size.\n\n### Motion\n\nIf step transitions animate:\n\n- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`.\n- Do not rely on animation to communicate step changes or validation state.\n\nWCAG: 2.3.3 Animation from Interactions.\n\n---\n\n## Content Accessibility Plan\n\n### Labels and Instructions\n\nEvery field must have a visible label. Placeholder text is not a label.\n\nExamples:\n\n- \u201cDate of birth\u201d\n- \u201cInsurance member ID\u201d\n- \u201cPrimary care provider\u201d\n- \u201cDo you have any allergies?\u201d\n\nFields with formatting requirements need persistent hints:\n\n- \u201cUse MM/DD/YYYY format.\u201d\n- \u201cEnter 10 digits, numbers only.\u201d\n- \u201cYou can find this number on your insurance card.\u201d\n\nHints must be connected with `aria-describedby`.\n\nWCAG: 1.3.1, 3.3.2.\n\n### Error Message Quality\n\nError messages must identify the field and suggest a fix.\n\nWeak:\n\n```text\nInvalid input.\n```\n\nStrong:\n\n```text\nError: Phone number must include 10 digits.\n```\n\nStrong:\n\n```text\nError: Insurance member ID is required. Enter the member ID from your insurance card.\n```\n\nFor sensitive healthcare fields, avoid blame-oriented wording. Use direct, neutral language.\n\nWCAG: 3.3.1, 3.3.3.\n\n### Link Text\n\nSummary links must be meaningful out of context.\n\nAcceptable:\n\n```text\nDate of birth is required.\nInsurance details: Member ID is required.\n```\n\nNot acceptable:\n\n```text\nFix this.\nClick here.\nRequired field.\n```\n\nWCAG: 2.4.4 Link Purpose.\n\n### Reading Order\n\nDOM order must match visual order:\n\n1. Step heading\n2. Error summary, if present\n3. Step instructions\n4. Field groups\n5. Step action buttons\n\nDo not visually move the error summary above the heading using CSS while leaving it later in the DOM.\n\nWCAG: 1.3.2 Meaningful Sequence.\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Automated Testing\n\nRun axe-core on these states:\n\n- Each step with no errors\n- Each step with one inline blur error\n- Each step with multiple submit-time errors\n- Final review with no errors\n- Final review with cross-step consolidated errors\n- 200% zoom visual pass\n- Narrow viewport pass\n\nExpected automated checks:\n\n- Labels are associated.\n- ARIA attributes are valid.\n- `aria-describedby` targets exist.\n- No duplicate IDs.\n- Contrast passes.\n- Heading order is logical.\n\nAxe will not fully prove:\n\n- Focus moved correctly.\n- Screen reader announcement timing is usable.\n- Cross-step error links focus the intended field.\n- Polite live region is not too noisy.\n\n### DOM Verification\n\nRequired DOM assertions:\n\n- Invalid input has `aria-invalid=\"true\"`.\n- Invalid input `aria-describedby` includes the error ID.\n- Error ID exists exactly once in the DOM.\n- Error summary has `role=\"alert\"` on submit-time validation.\n- Error summary has `tabindex=\"-1\"` and receives focus.\n- Summary link target maps to the actual input ID.\n- Current step indicator has `aria-current=\"step\"`.\n- Inline errors do not each have `role=\"alert\"`.\n\n### Keyboard Tests\n\nTest cases:\n\n- Tab through each step in logical order.\n- Continue with valid fields advances to next step and focuses the new step heading.\n- Continue with invalid fields keeps the user on the step and focuses the error summary.\n- Tab from summary to each error link.\n- Activate an error link and verify focus moves to the invalid input.\n- Shift+Tab order remains logical after error summary appears.\n- Final submit with cross-step errors focuses the consolidated summary.\n- Activate a cross-step error link and verify SPA navigation to the correct step and focus on the correct field.\n- Back navigation preserves values and errors.\n\n### Screen Reader Tests\n\nRun with NVDA, JAWS, and VoiceOver.\n\nScenarios:\n\n- Page announces main heading and current step.\n- Required fields are announced as required.\n- Invalid fields announce label, invalid state, hint, and error.\n- Blur-time validation does not interrupt aggressively.\n- Failed Continue announces the summary count.\n- Summary links are meaningful.\n- Cross-step summary links include step context.\n- After activating a summary link, focus lands on the invalid field and its error is available.\n\n### Visual Tests\n\n- Error is understandable without color.\n- Focus ring visible on inputs, buttons, summary container, and links.\n- Error messages wrap at narrow widths.\n- 200% zoom and 400% equivalent reflow do not hide fields or summaries.\n- High contrast mode preserves error icon/text and focus indicators.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Task 1: Field Error Association System\n\n\ud83d\udd0d **Review checkpoint after this task**\n\n**Files:**\n\n- Form field component(s)\n- Error message component\n- React Hook Form field wrapper utilities\n\n**Structure Stub:**\n\n```html\n<label for=\"[field-id]\">[Visible field label]</label>\n<p id=\"[field-id]-hint\">[Optional hint]</p>\n<input\n  id=\"[field-id]\"\n  name=\"[field-name]\"\n  aria-invalid=\"[true when invalid]\"\n  aria-describedby=\"[hint-id] [error-id when invalid]\"\n/>\n<p id=\"[field-id]-error\">\n  <span aria-hidden=\"true\">[error icon]</span>\n  Error: [specific fix-oriented message]\n</p>\n```\n\n**ARIA Attributes:**\n\n- `aria-invalid=\"true\"`: exposes invalid state. WCAG 3.3.1, 4.1.2.\n- `aria-describedby`: associates hint and error. WCAG 1.3.1, 3.3.2.\n- `aria-required` or native `required`: exposes required state. WCAG 3.3.2, 4.1.2.\n\n**Keyboard Interactions:**\n\n- Tab enters and exits fields in DOM order.\n- No focus stealing on blur validation.\n\n**Tests:**\n\n- Invalid field receives `aria-invalid`.\n- Error ID exists and is referenced by `aria-describedby`.\n- Valid field does not reference stale error text.\n- Error icon is non-color visual cue and hidden from AT if decorative.\n\n**WCAG Criteria:**\n\n- 1.3.1, 1.4.1, 3.3.1, 3.3.2, 3.3.3, 4.1.2.\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Blur-Time Validation Announcement Strategy\n\n\ud83d\udd0d **Review checkpoint after this task**\n\n**Files:**\n\n- Form-level validation status component\n- React Hook Form blur handling integration\n\n**Structure Stub:**\n\n```html\n<div id=\"form-validation-status\" role=\"status\" aria-live=\"polite\"></div>\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n\n- On blur, show inline error.\n- Update one shared polite status region with a short message.\n- Debounce updates by about 500ms.\n- Do not use per-field `role=\"alert\"`.\n\n**Tests:**\n\n- Blurring invalid field shows inline error.\n- Focus remains on next focused element.\n- Polite status updates once, not repeatedly.\n- Screen reader can access full error when returning to the field.\n\n**WCAG Criteria:**\n\n- 3.3.1, 3.3.3, 4.1.3, 2.4.3.\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Step-Level Error Summary\n\n\ud83d\udd0d **Review checkpoint after this task**\n\n**Files:**\n\n- Step error summary component\n- Step validation handler\n- Error link focus utility\n\n**Structure Stub:**\n\n```html\n<div\n  id=\"step-error-summary\"\n  role=\"alert\"\n  tabindex=\"-1\"\n  aria-labelledby=\"step-error-summary-heading\"\n>\n  <h3 id=\"step-error-summary-heading\">3 errors on this page</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li><a href=\"#field-id\">[Field label]: [error message]</a></li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n\n- Appears only after failed Continue or attempted step advancement.\n- Focus moves to summary after render.\n- Links focus the invalid input.\n- Summary count matches visible list count.\n\n**Tests:**\n\n- Continue with errors prevents step advancement.\n- Summary receives focus.\n- Summary announces count and links.\n- Each link moves focus to the corresponding input.\n\n**WCAG Criteria:**\n\n- 2.1.1, 2.4.3, 2.4.4, 3.3.1, 3.3.3, 4.1.3.\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Step Navigation and Focus Persistence\n\n\ud83d\udd0d **Review checkpoint after this task**\n\n**Files:**\n\n- Multi-step form controller\n- Step progress component\n- Focus intent utility\n\n**Structure Stub:**\n\n```html\n<nav aria-label=\"Registration progress\">\n  <ol>\n    <li><span aria-current=\"step\">Personal info</span></li>\n    <li><span>Insurance details</span></li>\n  </ol>\n</nav>\n\n<h2 tabindex=\"-1\">Step 2 of 4: Insurance details</h2>\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n\n- Successful Continue focuses next step heading.\n- Back preserves entered data and validation state.\n- Current step uses `aria-current=\"step\"`.\n- Failed Continue focuses summary instead of changing step.\n\n**Tests:**\n\n- Valid Continue moves focus to next step heading.\n- Back returns to previous step without clearing values.\n- Current step is programmatically identified.\n- Errors remain available when returning to a step.\n\n**WCAG Criteria:**\n\n- 1.3.1, 2.4.3, 2.4.6, 3.3.7, 4.1.2.\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Final Cross-Step Consolidated Error Summary\n\n\ud83d\udd0d **Review checkpoint after this task**\n\n**Files:**\n\n- Final review error summary component\n- Cross-step validation mapper\n- Cross-step focus/navigation utility\n\n**Structure Stub:**\n\n```html\n<div\n  id=\"final-error-summary\"\n  role=\"alert\"\n  tabindex=\"-1\"\n  aria-labelledby=\"final-error-summary-heading\"\n>\n  <h3 id=\"final-error-summary-heading\">\n    7 errors must be fixed before submitting\n  </h3>\n\n  <section aria-labelledby=\"insurance-errors-heading\">\n    <h4 id=\"insurance-errors-heading\">Insurance details</h4>\n    <ul>\n      <li>\n        <a href=\"#insurance-member-id\">\n          Insurance details: Member ID is required.\n        </a>\n      </li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n</div>\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n\n- On final submit failure, focus moves to final summary.\n- Errors are grouped by step.\n- Each link navigates to correct step and focuses the invalid field after render.\n- Link text includes step name, field name, and error.\n\n**Tests:**\n\n- Final submit with missing prior fields shows grouped summary.\n- Summary receives focus.\n- Cross-step link changes step and focuses target field.\n- Target field announces its label and error.\n\n**WCAG Criteria:**\n\n- 2.1.1, 2.4.3, 2.4.4, 3.3.1, 3.3.3, 4.1.3.\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Visual Error and Focus Treatment\n\n\ud83d\udd0d **Review checkpoint after this task**\n\n**Files:**\n\n- Form CSS/module styles\n- Design system field styles\n- Error summary styles\n\n**Requirements:**\n\n- Red treatment remains.\n- Add icon or \u201cError:\u201d text.\n- Contrast passes for text and UI boundaries.\n- Focus indicators visible on all controls and summaries.\n- Layout works at 200% zoom and narrow widths.\n\n**Tests:**\n\n- Error state is understandable in grayscale/high contrast.\n- Focus ring visible on all interactive elements.\n- Error summary and long messages wrap.\n- No horizontal scroll at narrow viewport.\n\n**WCAG Criteria:**\n\n- 1.4.1, 1.4.3, 1.4.10, 1.4.11, 2.4.7, 2.4.11, 2.5.8.\n\n---\n\n## a11y-Critic Review Checkpoints\n\n| Checkpoint | After Task | Focus Areas |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Field Error Association System | Verify `aria-invalid`, `aria-describedby`, stable IDs, visible labels, non-color indicator |\n| 2 | Blur-Time Validation | Verify no aggressive per-field alerts, polite shared status, no focus stealing |\n| 3 | Step Error Summary | Verify `role=\"alert\"`, focus movement, link text, link-to-field behavior |\n| 4 | Step Navigation | Verify focus order, `aria-current=\"step\"`, data persistence, heading focus |\n| 5 | Final Cross-Step Summary | Verify grouped errors, cross-step navigation, post-render field focus |\n| 6 | Visual Treatment | Verify contrast, focus visibility, non-color error identification, zoom/reflow |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\nThe implementation should consist of:\n\n- Reusable accessible field wrapper\n- Inline error message component\n- Shared polite validation status region\n- Step-level assertive error summary\n- Final cross-step error summary\n- Focus intent utility for summary links and step transitions\n- Step progress component with `aria-current=\"step\"`\n\nARIA patterns used:\n\n- Native form controls\n- APG Button pattern\n- Native link pattern\n- Status/alert regions for validation messaging\n\nNo APG Tabs, Dialog, Menu, or Disclosure pattern is required unless the existing UI uses those widgets separately.\n\n---\n\n## Failure Modes This Plan Prevents\n\n- Red-only error indication failing WCAG 1.4.1.\n- Error text visible but not associated with the input.\n- `aria-label` on error text instead of `aria-describedby` from the input.\n- Assertive screen reader interruptions after every blur event.\n- Error summary appearing visually while focus remains on Continue.\n- Summary links scrolling but not moving focus.\n- Cross-step final errors that cannot navigate to the actual field.\n- Duplicate or unstable error IDs after React re-render.\n- Current step conveyed only visually.\n- Stale errors remaining in `aria-describedby` after correction.\n- Tests that verify visuals but not rendered ARIA placement.\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- WAI-ARIA Authoring Practices Guide: https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/\n- APG Button Pattern: https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/button/\n- WCAG 2.2 Quick Reference: https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/quickref/\n- WCAG 3.3.1 Error Identification\n- WCAG 3.3.2 Labels or Instructions\n- WCAG 3.3.3 Error Suggestion\n- WCAG 4.1.3 Status Messages\n- WCAG 1.4.1 Use of Color\n- WCAG 2.4.3 Focus Order",
